 GLOBACOM has felicitated with Muslims on the 2020 Eid-el-Kabir festival. In a statement issued on Thursrday, it urged the faithful to make moderation their watchword as they celebrate and ensure compliance with the COVID-19 safety precautions of staying at home, observing physical distancing, washing hands regularly and using hand sanitisers. Globacom enjoined the Muslim Ummah to take the opportunity of this yearâ€™s celebration to pray for the unity, peace and development of Nigeria as well as the restoration of normalcy to the entire world currently ravaged by the COVID-19 pandemic.